    "text": "Multiple members of the Quinlan community are working on a benefit event to help the family of Jonathan Morrill who passed away on Friday morning.\nFor the last six years, Morrill welcomed customers at his restaurant, Mama’s Family Cafe, in Quinlan.\n“He was dealing with a lot of health problems, he went through three recent surgeries and his body just gave out,” Morrill’s friend and organizer of the event Mike Kline said. “What we’re wanting to do with the benefit is raise money to help his family with his funeral expenses.”\nThe benefit is scheduled for Dec. 7 from 3 p.m. “until dark” at Mama’s Family Cafe at 2382 East Quinlan Parkway. It will feature lunch plates with brisket and hot dog plates for sale and live music by blues-rock band Crazy Uncle Bill and local Christian rapper 333 Malo (aka Malachi Stone).\nThe benefit will also include vendors, raffles and drawings, a live auction and a cake walk.\nThose interested in being vendors at the event or donating items for the raffle, auction or cake walk can message Kline through his Facebook page at [https://tinyurl.com/2da4a28u](https://tinyurl.com/2da4a28u).",
